                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Setup with differential calorimeter is shown in Fig. 2 and extends the earlier work [6]. One channel is used for experiments, the second channel represents a control sensor. Each channel has "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "15\\mathrm{ml}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " of water in Dewar vacuum flask with NTC thermistor immersed in the fluid. Additionally, the air temperature is monitored in each section of the calorimeter inside and outside of the thermo- insulating box. Stabilized power supply is also measured by a separate sensor, the delta- sigma ADC with 24 bit sampling is used. In this work we utilize a passive scheme for the calorimeter, where a slow temperature variation is provided by a circadian rhythm in the laboratory (about 1- 1.5 "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "^\\circ \\mathrm{C}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " for 24 hours) and guaranties a high degree of homogeneity in temperature distribution. Differences caused by changes in the heat capacity of water samples are measured as symmetry breaks between channels, small fluctuations about "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "10^{- 5}^\\circ \\mathrm{C}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        2122,
                                        2314,
                                        3115
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " of relative temperature can be detected. This system is used to explore the heat capacity of para- and ortho- isomers of water [25]. In several experiments we use electrochemical impedance spectrometers [30] to detect effects on environmental sensors, see Fig. 7."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
